at|^^|cp||at|^b|
at|^^|cp||at|^bCohen's system of the cheapest of 2N and the 4th suit as indicating that responder has a weak hand that cannot force to game is played by many. But it is flawed in my opinion because it forces responder to make an artificial bid that may get your side too high when, in fact, you want to stay low. I play what I feel is a much sounder, more natural, and easier to remember system. It is described fully in my movie on reverses|
